text: Hikaru Mori (born 7 July 1999) is a female Japanese individual and synchronised trampoline gymnast. She won the silver medal in the women's individual event at the 2018 Asian Games held in Jakarta, Indonesia. In 2018, she also won the gold medal in the women's synchro event, alongside Megu Uyama, at the 2018 Trampoline Gymnastics World Championships held in Saint Petersburg, Russia.
